A 10-year-old child was killed instantly after a taxi rammed into his home, knocking the child and two other children while they were sleeping in their beds this morning. Chatsworth police spokesperson Captain Cheryl Pillay said the taxi driver rammed into the home in Burlington, Chatsworth, and thereafter fled the scene, Rising Sun Chatsworth reported. One child succumbed to his injuries at the scene. Two children, aged 12 and 14, sustained injuries and were transported to a local hospital. The driver fled the scene, added Pillay. Chatsworth police are investigating a case of culpable homicide and related charges in terms of the National Road Traffic Act. &#8211; Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.